# TickingAreaErrorReason Enumeration

> [!CAUTION]
> This enum is still in pre-release.  Its signature may change or it may be removed in future releases.

The reason that the {@link @minecraft/server.TickingAreaError} was thrown.

## Constants
### **IdentifierAlreadyExists**
`IdentifierAlreadyExists = "IdentifierAlreadyExists"`

Added a ticking area with an identifier that already exists.
### **OverChunkLimit**
`OverChunkLimit = "OverChunkLimit"`

 Adding this ticking area pushed the ticking areas over the limit specified by [*@minecraft/server.TickingAreaManager.maxChunkCount*](../../../scriptapi/minecraft/server/TickingAreaManager.md#maxchunkcount).
### **SideLengthExceeded**
`SideLengthExceeded = "SideLengthExceeded"`

Exceeded the 255 chunk limit for the length or width of the ticking area.
### **UnknownIdentifier**
`UnknownIdentifier = "UnknownIdentifier"`

Tried to remove ticking area with identifier not registered in the [*@minecraft/server.TickingAreaManager*](../../../scriptapi/minecraft/server/TickingAreaManager.md).
